<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFF5821D644BCFC5A" bold="true" box="[198,717,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Distribution, Habitat and Conservation:</emphasis>
—Endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="32DA09B3FFBF8D3BFC1C21D645BDFC5A" box="[898,972,906,932]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, this species is known only from the Espinhaço Range, in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="880987C1FFBF8D3BFD8221ED4411FC35" box="[540,608,945,971]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Bahia</collectingRegion>
(Map 1), and occurs in campos rupestres and cerrado vegetation. Due to insufficient data about population size, 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFD162184450FFC0F" authorityName="Buril" authorityYear="2012" box="[648,894,984,1009]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grisea">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFD162184450FFC0F" box="[648,894,984,1009]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Jacquemontia grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered as Data Deficient (DD) according to the 
<bibRefCitation id="2E5C34D2FFBF8D3BFEC521A24786FBE6" author="IUCN" box="[347,503,1022,1048]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" refId="ref2822" refString="IUCN (2001) IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. IUCN Species Survival Commission. - IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, United Kingdom." type="book" year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
criteria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="02D71AA8FFBF8D3BFF58267944B9FA16" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4A724923FFBF8D3BFF5826794584FB98" blockId="2.[151,1436,404,1512]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFF5826794726FBC1" bold="true" box="[198,343,1061,1087]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFD9A2679443CFBC0" authorityName="Buril" authorityYear="2012" box="[516,589,1061,1086]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grisea">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFD9A2679443CFBC0" box="[516,589,1061,1086]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(from Latin), refers to the pure greyish (sometimes verging on bluish) colour of its leaves, which is apparent on live plants and dried specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A724923FFBF8D3BFF58262E4557FAB0" blockId="2.[151,1436,404,1512]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFF58262E4707FB72" bold="true" box="[198,374,1138,1164]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Observations:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFE0D262F44F8FB72" authorityName="Buril" authorityYear="2012" box="[403,649,1139,1164]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grisea">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFE0D262F44F8FB72" box="[403,649,1139,1164]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Jacquemontia grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFCB9262F42D4FB72" authority="Ooststr." authorityName="Ooststr." box="[807,1189,1138,1164]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFCB9262F4232FB72" box="[807,1091,1139,1164]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Jacquemontia decipiens</emphasis>
Ooststr.
</taxonomicName>
which is endemic to the southern part of the Espinhaço Range in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="880987C1FFBF8D3BFCAD26C545A7FB4D" box="[819,982,1177,1203]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
. It differs by the presence of T-shaped and very long trichomes (vs. 5–6-armed trichomes in 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFCD8269C45ACFB27" box="[838,989,1216,1241]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFCD8269C45ACFB27" box="[838,989,1216,1241]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">J. decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and capitulliform, multi-flowered inflorescences (vs. inflorescences with up to 7 flowers, and sometimes with a few axillary flowers, in 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFA1926BB477DFAD8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFA1926BB477DFAD8" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">J. decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In addition, bracts occur in 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFD1D2751449FFAD8" authorityName="Buril" authorityYear="2012" box="[643,750,1293,1318]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grisea">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFD1D2751449FFAD8" box="[643,750,1293,1318]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">J. grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFC4E27514212FAD8" box="[976,1123,1293,1318]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFC4E27514212FAD8" box="[976,1123,1293,1318]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">J. decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the outer sepals are oblanceolate in 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFECE276847C4FAB3" authorityName="Buril" authorityYear="2012" box="[336,437,1332,1357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grisea">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFECE276847C4FAB3" box="[336,437,1332,1357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">J. grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(vs. lanceolate in 
<taxonomicName id="8DCD32A0FFBF8D3BFD1527684567FAB3" box="[651,790,1332,1357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Jacquemontia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="78B99531FFBF8D3BFD1527684567FAB3" box="[651,790,1332,1357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">J. decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
